-- Wall St. snaps back with rally
-- 
-- Wed Aug 1, 2007 4:39pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/01/us-stocks-idUSPAR17287220070801

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Stocks ended higher after a late-day rally in a sharply volatile session on Wednesday as investors bought shares beaten down in the recent sell-off related to credit worries. 

 Based on the latest available data, the Dow Jones industrial average rose 150.38 points, or 1.14 percent, to end unofficially at 13,362.37. The Standard & Poor's 500 Index was up 10.54 points, or 0.72 percent, to finish unofficially at 1,465.81. The Nasdaq Composite Index was up 7.60 points, or 0.30 percent, to close unofficially at 2,553.87.